31
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:38,360
Even if Ti Cha
cheated with your best friend,

32
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,880
you shouldn't look this heartbroken.

33
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:43,240
Inspector Huo,
you aren't just after the truth.

34
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:44,760
And also in charge of
mending broken hearts?

35
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,040
Your clothes are wet.

36
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:51,640
You'll get sick if you don't change.

37
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:56,320
Please keep your distance.

38
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:04,640
Whatever I want,

39
00:03:04,640 --> 00:03:06,560
they'll hand it over without hesitation.

40
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:10,160
Don't even think about it.

41
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:26,080
The missing Ye Ying.

42
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:28,080
The amnesiac An Ning.

43
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:30,600
Was it just an accident,

44
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:32,680
or a well-planned coincidence?

45
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:38,800
Inspector.

46
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,360
This is the original file
on Ye Hong's death report.

47
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,120
As you instructed,

48
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:44,720
everyone who knew about Ye Hong's death

49
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:45,720
has been placed under watch.

50
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:49,280
The fish won't bite.

51
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:51,520
It means the bait isn't big enough.

52
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,440
From now on,

53
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,720
Ye Hong has come back to life.

54
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,800
Let's see

55
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,120
how tough

56
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:05,600
Ye Ying's heart is.

57
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,760
According to reliable sources,

58
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:16,160
Ye Hong, the gang leader,

59
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:17,600
was attacked within his gang

60
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,760
and seriously injured a few days ago.

61
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:20,040
He was badly hurt but still alive.

62
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:22,360
He's now being treated
at a private hospital.

63
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:24,320
Sources close to the case revealed

64
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,720
that this incident is highly likely

65
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:27,280
an act of deliberate revenge.

66
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:30,120
Those reporters are pretty capable.

67
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:31,840
I kept everything so low‑key.

68
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:33,880
Yet they still managed to
dig out the story.

69
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:48,800
What are you thinking about?

70
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:50,480
So engrossed.

71
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:51,560
What I'm thinking about

72
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,440
is none of your business.

73
00:04:58,080 --> 00:05:02,040
You demanded 24-hour close protection.

74
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:06,360
So of course I have to
keep an eye on you.

75
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,360
Look.

76
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:13,120
The eggs are about to burn.

77
00:05:19,880 --> 00:05:20,680
I'm warning you.

78
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,600
Don't mess around.

79
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:22,560
Be careful, or I'll...

80
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,160
You'll do what?

81
00:05:26,350 --> 00:05:27,980
♪Falling in love♪

82
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:29,480
Kill me

83
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,960
or arrest me?

84
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:38,520
♪Catch me, I'm falling for you♪

85
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:41,640
Cut the smooth talk.

86
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:43,960
I truly hate what you do.

87
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:46,700
♪Everyday, every night♪

88
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:51,000
But why is there

89
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:54,600
a hint of panic in your eyes?

90
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:06,880
Don't misunderstand.

91
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:09,160
I was out of line yesterday.

92
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:12,240
I'm here to apologize.

93
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,040
I don't accept

94
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,600
an after-the-fact apology.

95
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:46,240
It's okay.

96
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:48,320
I can wait.

97
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:54,040
I have plenty of patience

98
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:56,320
to wait for your forgiveness.

99
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:10,040
[Century Hospital]

100
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:17,560
[Operating Room/Ward]

101
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:18,400
Inspector.

102
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:20,360
Ye Ying still hasn't shown up.

103
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:21,600
Could it be…

104
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:23,160
our judgment is wrong?

105
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:29,760
[Operating Room/Ward]

106
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,040
She's here.

107
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:38,480
We'll have the answer soon.

108
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:45,200
[Dr. Aamir Kan; Patient: Ye Hong]

109
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:15,040
Police investigation.

110
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:15,560
Go.

111
00:08:18,520 --> 00:08:19,840
Neuroscience Department.

112
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:23,120
She's here for a follow-up exam.

113
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,680
The appointment time is…

114
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:25,720
[Patient Info: An Ning,
Date of Report: 2025.09.20]

115
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,760
Three days ago?

116
00:08:26,760 --> 00:08:27,720
But back then…

117
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:30,320
we hadn't even started planning yet.

118
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,760
[Century Hospital, Aamir Kan]

119
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,160
What do you do?

120
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:51,080
Making rounds.

121
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:18,320
It seems the mastermind

122
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:20,760
couldn't wait to silence Ye Hong.

123
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:22,400
So that means

124
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,760
An Ning's appearance
was really a coincidence.

125
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:25,760
Anyway.

126
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:27,680
Keep tracking

127
00:09:28,160 --> 00:09:29,200
Ye Ying's whereabouts.

128
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:30,600
Okay.

129
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,160
Mom, Dad.

130
00:09:40,160 --> 00:09:41,120
[Elder Sister-in-Law]
We're back.

131
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:43,800
Hey sweet girl, you're here.

132
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:46,200
I came back as soon as you called.

133
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:47,560
Grandma, Xuan.

134
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:48,920
So sweet.

135
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,640
Mom.

136
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:52,720
This is for you.

137
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,960
It's pure gold.

138
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:55,600
Thank you, my dear girl.

139
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:57,920
Dad.

140
00:09:59,000 --> 00:09:59,760
I specially bought this

141
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:01,360
at a high price

142
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:03,160
from Cuba.

143
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:05,000
It's a limited edition now.

144
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:06,400
Good.

145
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:07,320
Sis.

146
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:08,360
What about mine?

147
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:09,240
Hold on, don't rush.

148
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:14,200
A specially made
thousand-year-old ginseng.

149
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:17,240
Sis, you spent so much.

150
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:19,160
This one's even better.

151
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:22,520
Fresh deer whip.

152
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,600
Eat this,

153
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:26,680
and you'll boost your fertility.

154
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,040
Thanks a lot.

155
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:31,480
Take these to every room.

156
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:35,040
Married a wife who can't bear kids.

157
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,520
Even magic pills are useless.

158
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:37,640
All she knows is draining our energy.

159
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:38,400
Mom.

160
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:40,440
You can't just say that.

161
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,040
That hen that doesn't lay eggs

162
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:43,520
is still a chicken, isn't it?

163
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:46,000
We can still keep it for the meat.

164
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,640
Or make some soup with it.

165
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:50,080
A disobedient hen needs to be tamed.

166
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:52,920
I came this time to help you
teach it properly.

167
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:55,960
Hmph, just wait and see
how I deal with you.

168
00:10:57,280 --> 00:11:00,440
Let's see what tricks you can pull now.

169
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:13,520
Auntie.

170
00:11:13,520 --> 00:11:15,720
My kite got stuck in a tree.

171
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:17,720
Can you help me get it down?

172
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:36,360
Mom said you took a lot of money
from our family.

173
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:37,640
She said you're a very bad person.

174
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:39,240
Once you're gone,

175
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,360
we can get our money back.

176
00:11:52,630 --> 00:11:59,730
